{
  "batch": "Architecture & Coupling",
  "batch_index": 1,
  "assessments": {
    "cross_module_architecture": 78.0,
    "high_level_elegance": 82.0
  },
  "dimension_notes": {
    "cross_module_architecture": {
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go` defines transport action tokens and metadata in `uploadActionMetas`/`c2cActionMetas`.",
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/service.go` defines a separate `uploadActionDescriptors` table that must duplicate the same action universe in order to build dispatcher behavior.",
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/service.go:newUploadDispatcher` dynamically reconciles these two sources at runtime and errors only if they diverge."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "medium"
    },
    "high_level_elegance": {
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/service.go` keeps package-level mutable error templates such as `errOpenEndpointRequestRequired`, then sets `Action` per call in `ValidateCommand` before returning.",
        "The validation path (`validateAction` + `ValidateCommand`) mutates shared objects and returns by value, which creates hidden mutable cross-call behavior and makes concurrency correctness dependent on call serialization."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "action_contract_dual_sources",
      "summary": "Upload action ownership is split across protocol metadata and upload service descriptors, creating brittle cross-module coupling.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`actions.go` exposes supported upload actions via `uploadActionMetas` and parser metadata.",
        "`service.go` independently encodes dispatch behavior in `uploadActionDescriptors` with `action`, `execute`, `description`, and `operation`.",
        "`newUploadDispatcher` builds a runtime map and only detects mismatches at construction time, so coherence is enforced indirectly rather than through a shared abstraction."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a single source of truth for upload action contracts (for example, a typed action registry in `protocol/actions` that includes both token and operation/dispatch metadata), and have `uploadsvc` consume it directly rather than maintaining duplicated action tables.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "action_contract_duplication"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
      "identifier": "validation_error_singletons_mutated",
      "summary": "Reusable error templates are mutated in-place during validation, creating hidden shared state and potential cross-request contamination.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Package-level vars like `errOpenEndpointRequestRequired` and `errResetRequestRequired` are declared once and reused.",
        "`ValidateCommand` sets `errX.Action = cmd.Action` before returning, which mutates shared state.",
        "These errors are shared across all callers of `ValidateCommand`, so concurrent command validation can race and leak incorrect `Action` labels."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace mutable package-level error instances with local construction (`return CommandValidationError{Action: cmd.Action, Problem: ...}`) at each failure site, or helper constructors that return new values so validation is stateless and concurrency-safe.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "shared_mutable_validation_state"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Action contract is maintained in parallel data structures across modules without an explicit shared model.",
      "Validation layer relies on shared, mutable templates instead of immutable per-call error values."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "action_contract_dual_sources",
      "validation_error_singletons_mutated"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
}


